23 SECTION 28. IC 6-3.6-6-12, AS AMENDED BY P.L.230-2025,
24 SECTION 82, IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2027]. Sec. 12.
25 (a) Except as provided in this chapter and IC 6-3.6-11, this section
26 applies to an allocation of certified shares in all counties.
27 (b) The allocation amount of a civil taxing unit during a calendar
28 year must be based on the amounts for the calendar year preceding the
29 distribution year and is equal to the amount determined using the
30 following formula:
31 STEP ONE: Determine the sum of the total property taxes being
32 imposed by the civil taxing unit.
33 STEP TWO: Determine the sum of the following:
34 (A) Amounts appropriated from property taxes to pay the
35 principal of or interest on any debenture or other debt
36 obligation issued after June 30, 2005, other than an obligation
37 described in subsection (c).
38 (B) Amounts appropriated from property taxes to make
39 payments on any lease entered into after June 30, 2005, other
40 than a lease described in subsection (d).
41 STEP THREE: Subtract the STEP TWO amount from the STEP
42 ONE amount.
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

28
1 STEP FOUR: In the case of a qualifying municipality as defined
2 in IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(d) that is located in a county described in
3 IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(a), and only for the allocation of certified shares
4 in 2027 and 2028, STEP THREE multiplied by seventy percent
5 (70%).
6 STEP FIVE: Determine the sum of:
7 (A) the:
8 (i) STEP THREE amount; or
9 (ii) STEP FOUR amount in the case of a qualifying
10 municipality as defined in IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(d) that is located
11 in a county described in IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(a);
12 (B) the civil taxing unit's certified shares plus the amount
13 distributed under section 3(a)(2) of this chapter for the
14 previous calendar year; plus
15 (C) in the case of a qualifying municipality as defined in
16 IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(d) that is located in a county described in
17 IC 6-1.1-18.5-31(a), and only for the allocation of certified
18 shares in 2026, the amount of the levy for the municipality's
19 debt service and lease rental funds that was certified in 2025
20 multiplied by fifty-four and five-tenths percent (54.5%). This
21 clause expires January 1, 2027.
22 The allocation amount is subject to adjustment as provided in
23 IC 36-8-19-7.5.
24 (c) Except as provided in this subsection, an appropriation for the
25 calendar year preceding the distribution year from property taxes to
26 repay interest and principal of a debt obligation is not deducted from
27 the allocation amount for a civil taxing unit if:
28 (1) the debt obligation was issued; and
29 (2) the proceeds were appropriated from property taxes;
30 to refund or otherwise refinance a debt obligation or a lease issued
31 before July 1, 2005. However, an appropriation from property taxes
32 related to a debt obligation issued after June 30, 2005, is deducted if
33 the debt extends payments on a debt or lease beyond the time in which
34 the debt or lease would have been payable if the debt or lease had not
35 been refinanced or increases the total amount that must be paid on a
36 debt or lease in excess of the amount that would have been paid if the
37 debt or lease had not been refinanced. The amount of the deduction is
38 the annual amount for each year of the extension period or the annual
39 amount of the increase over the amount that would have been paid.
40 (d) Except as provided in this subsection, an appropriation for the
41 calendar year preceding the distribution year from property taxes to
42 make payments on a lease is not deducted from the allocation amount
