25 officer of the office of the department that administers programs
26 of state and federal aid to local units of government, or the officer's
27 designee.
28 Sec. 39. "State highway system" means the system of highways
29 and streets that are of general economic importance to Indiana as
30 a whole and for which responsibility is assigned to the department.
31 Sec. 40. "Substantial completion" refers to the date, as
32 determined by the department, when the construction of the
33 contract is sufficiently completed in accordance with the plans and
34 specifications, as modified by any change orders, so that the
35 construction can be used for its intended purpose.
36 Sec. 41. "Transportation plan" means a statement evaluating
37 transportation policy objectives and projecting specific long range
38 comprehensive actions to accomplish policy objectives.
39 Sec. 42. "Traveled way" means the part of the roadway for the
40 movement of vehicles. The term does not include shoulders or
41 auxiliary lanes.
42 Sec. 43. "Trimovement sign" means a sign that displays three
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

38
1 (3) separate images sequentially by rotating triangular cylinders.
2 Sec. 44. (a) "Unzoned commercial or industrial area" means an
3 adjacent area not zoned under state or local statute, rule, or
4 ordinance on which there is located one (1) or more permanent
5 structures for commercial or industrial activities other than a sign
6 or upon which a commercial or an industrial activity is actually
7 conducted, whether or not there is a permanent structure located
8 upon the adjacent area, and the area:
9 (1) extending six hundred (600) feet beyond the edge of the
10 commercial or industrial activity as determined under
11 subsection (c); and
12 (2) located along either side of an interstate or a primary
13 highway.
14 The term does not include land contiguous to an interstate or a
15 primary highway that has been designated as scenic by the state.
16 (b) The term does not include the following areas:
17 (1) Within three hundred (300) feet of a building used
18 primarily as a residence, unless the owner of the building
19 consents in writing to the particular commercial use.
20 (2) Within five hundred (500) feet of the following:
21 (A) A public park garden.
22 (B) A recreation area or forest preserve.
23 (C) A church or school.
24 (D) An officially designated historic battlefield, museum,
25 or historical monument.
26 (E) A safety rest or recreation area, publicly owned,
27 controlled, and maintained under 23 U.S.C. 319.
28 (F) A sanitary or other facility for the accommodation of
29 motorists, publicly owned, controlled, and maintained
30 under 23 U.S.C. 319.
