17 SECTION 55. IC 11-8-8-7, AS AMENDED BY THE TECHNICAL
18 CORRECTIONS BILL OF THE 2026 GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IS
19 AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]:
20 Sec. 7. (a) Subject to section 19 of this chapter, the following persons
21 must register under this chapter:
22 (1) A sex or violent offender who resides in Indiana. A sex or
23 violent offender resides in Indiana if either of the following
24 applies:
25 (A) The sex or violent offender spends or intends to spend at
26 least seven (7) days (including part of a day) in Indiana during
27 a one hundred eighty (180) day period.
28 (B) The sex or violent offender owns real property in Indiana
29 and returns to Indiana at any time.
30 (2) A sex or violent offender who works or carries on a vocation
31 or intends to work or carry on a vocation full time or part time: for
32 a period:
33 (A) for a period exceeding seven (7) consecutive days; or
34 (B) for a total period exceeding fourteen (14) days;
35 during any calendar year in Indiana regardless of whether the sex
36 or violent offender is financially compensated, volunteered, or is
37 acting for the purpose of government or educational benefit.
38 (3) A sex or violent offender who is enrolled or intends to be
39 enrolled on a full-time or part-time basis in any public or private
40 educational institution, including any secondary school, trade, or
41 professional institution, or postsecondary educational institution.
42 (b) Except as provided in subsection (e), a sex or violent offender
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

57
1 who resides in Indiana shall register with the local law enforcement
2 authority in the county where the sex or violent offender resides. If a
3 sex or violent offender resides in more than one (1) county, the sex or
4 violent offender shall register with the local law enforcement authority
5 in each county in which the sex or violent offender resides. If the sex
6 or violent offender is also required to register under subsection (a)(2)
7 or (a)(3), the sex or violent offender shall also register with the local
8 law enforcement authority in the county in which the offender is
9 required to register under subsection (c) or (d).
10 (c) A sex or violent offender described in subsection (a)(2) shall
11 register with the local law enforcement authority in the county where
12 the sex or violent offender is or intends to be employed or carry on a
13 vocation. If a sex or violent offender is or intends to be employed or
14 carry on a vocation in more than one (1) county, the sex or violent
15 offender shall register with the local law enforcement authority in each
16 county. If the sex or violent offender is also required to register under
17 subsection (a)(1) or (a)(3), the sex or violent offender shall also register
18 with the local law enforcement authority in the county in which the
19 offender is required to register under subsection (b) or (d).
20 (d) A sex or violent offender described in subsection (a)(3) shall
21 register with the local law enforcement authority in the county where
22 the sex or violent offender is enrolled or intends to be enrolled as a
23 student. If the sex or violent offender is also required to register under
24 subsection (a)(1) or (a)(2), the sex or violent offender shall also register
25 with the local law enforcement authority in the county in which the
26 offender is required to register under subsection (b) or (c).
27 (e) A sex or violent offender described in subsection (a)(1)(B) shall
28 register with the local law enforcement authority in the county in which
29 the real property is located. If the sex or violent offender is also
30 required to register under subsection (a)(1)(A), (a)(2), or (a)(3), the sex
31 or violent offender shall also register with the local law enforcement
32 authority in the county in which the offender is required to register
33 under subsection (b), (c), or (d).
34 (f) A sex or violent offender committed to the department shall
35 register with the department before the sex or violent offender is placed
36 in a community transition program, placed in a work release program,
37 or released from incarceration, whichever occurs first. The department
38 shall forward the sex or violent offender's registration information to
39 the local law enforcement authority of every county in which the sex or
40 violent offender is required to register. If a sex or violent offender
41 released from the department under this subsection:
42 (1) informs the department of the offender's intended location of
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

58
1 residence upon release; and
2 (2) does not move to this location upon release;
3 the offender shall, not later than seventy-two (72) hours after the date
4 on which the offender is released, report in person to the local law
5 enforcement authority having jurisdiction over the offender's current
6 address or location.
7 (g) This subsection does not apply to a sex or violent offender who
8 is a sexually violent predator. A sex or violent offender not committed
9 to the department shall register not more than seven (7) days after the
10 sex or violent offender:
11 (1) is released from a penal facility (as defined in
12 IC 35-31.5-2-232);
13 (2) is released from a secure private facility (as defined in
