16 (4) is transferred to a community transition program;
17 (5) is placed on parole;
18 (6) is placed on probation;
19 (7) is placed on home detention; or
20 (8) arrives at the place where the sex or violent offender is
21 required to register under subsection (b), (c), or (d);
22 whichever occurs first. A sex or violent offender required to register in
23 more than one (1) county under subsection (b), (c), (d), or (e) shall
24 register in each appropriate county not more than seventy-two (72)
25 hours after the sex or violent offender's arrival in that county or
26 acquisition of real estate in that county.
27 (h) This subsection applies to a sex or violent offender who is a
28 sexually violent predator. A sex or violent offender who is a sexually
29 violent predator shall register not more than seventy-two (72) hours
30 after the sex or violent offender:
31 (1) is released from a penal facility (as defined in
32 IC 35-31.5-2-232);
33 (2) is released from a secure private facility (as defined in
34 IC 31-9-2-115); IC 31-9-2.1-223);
35 (3) is released from a juvenile detention facility;
36 (4) is transferred to a community transition program;
37 (5) is placed on parole;
38 (6) is placed on probation;
39 (7) is placed on home detention; or
40 (8) arrives at the place where the sexually violent predator is
41 required to register under subsection (b), (c), or (d);
42 whichever occurs first. A sex or violent offender who is a sexually
