17 the department at least one (1) time per year.
18 (2) Contact each offender who is designated a sexually violent
19 predator in a manner approved or prescribed by the department at
20 least once every ninety (90) days.
21 (3) Personally visit each sex or violent offender in the county at
22 the sex or violent offender's listed address at least one (1) time per
23 year, beginning seven (7) days after the local law enforcement
24 authority receives a notice under section 7 of this chapter or the
25 date the sex or violent offender is:
26 (A) released from a penal facility (as defined in
27 IC 35-31.5-2-232), a secure private facility (as defined in
28 IC 31-9-2-115), IC 31-9-2.1-223), or a juvenile detention
29 facility;
30 (B) placed in a community transition program;
31 (C) placed in a community corrections program;
32 (D) placed on parole; or
33 (E) placed on probation;
34 whichever occurs first.
35 (4) Personally visit each sex or violent offender who is designated
36 a sexually violent predator under IC 35-38-1-7.5 at least once
37 every ninety (90) days, beginning seven (7) days after the local
38 law enforcement authority receives a notice under section 7 of
39 this chapter or the date the sex or violent offender is:
40 (A) released from a penal facility (as defined in
41 IC 35-31.5-2-232), a secure private facility (as defined in
42 IC 31-9-2-115), IC 31-9-2.1-223), or a juvenile detention
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

62
1 facility;
2 (B) placed in a community transition program;
3 (C) placed in a community corrections program;
4 (D) placed on parole; or
5 (E) placed on probation;
6 whichever occurs first.
7 (b) If a sex or violent offender appears not to reside at the sex or
8 violent offender's listed address, the local law enforcement authority
9 shall immediately notify the department and the prosecuting attorney.
10 SECTION 58. IC 11-10-4-1 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
