63
1 (e) The department may permit an offender committed to the
2 department to remain within a treatment facility operated by the
3 department for not more than fourteen (14) days past the offender's
4 mandatory release date, if:
5 (1) the offender has a serious physical or mental disorder or
6 disability;
7 (2) the offender is being held in the treatment facility operated by
8 the department until the offender may be placed in a similar
9 treatment setting outside the department;
10 (3) the department made a good faith effort to timely place the
11 offender in a treatment setting outside the department on or before
12 the offender's mandatory release date; and
13 (4) the offender:
14 (A) consents to being held in a treatment facility operated by
15 the department beyond the offender's mandatory release date;
16 or
17 (B) has been ordered by a court to be committed to a treatment
18 setting outside the department.
