11 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 11. (a) The office may assess community
12 residential facilities for the developmentally disabled (as defined in
13 IC 12-7-2-61) IC 12-7-2.1-118) and intermediate care facilities for
14 individuals with intellectual disabilities (ICF/IID) (as defined in
15 IC 16-29-4-2) that are not operated by the state in an amount not to
16 exceed ten percent (10%) of the total annual revenue of the facility for
17 the facility's preceding fiscal year.
18 (b) The assessments shall be paid to the office of Medicaid policy
19 and planning in equal monthly amounts on or before the tenth day of
20 each calendar month. The office may withhold Medicaid payments to
21 a provider described in subsection (a) that fails to pay an assessment
22 within thirty (30) days after the due date. The amount withheld may not
23 exceed the amount of the assessments due.
24 (c) Revenue from the assessments shall be credited to a special
25 account within the state general fund to be called the Medicaid
26 assessment account. Money in the account may be used only for
27 services for which federal financial participation under Medicaid is
28 available to match state funds. An amount equivalent to the federal
29 financial participation estimated to be received for services financed
30 from assessments under subsection (a) shall be used to finance
31 Medicaid services provided by facilities described in subsection (a).
32 (d) If federal financial participation to match the assessments in
33 subsection (a) becomes unavailable under federal law, the authority to
