10 SECTION 85. IC 12-17.2-7.6-3, AS ADDED BY P.L.92-2024,
11 SECTION 28, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
12 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) Not later than January 1, 2025, after
13 soliciting and considering recommendations from appropriate
14 stakeholders, the office of the secretary shall develop a regulatory
15 model that:
16 (1) is applicable only to micro facilities;
17 (2) incorporates waivers or variances from the office of the
18 secretary's rules applicable to providers under this article; and
19 (3) provides for a balance between the goals of:
20 (A) increasing the availability of child care, particularly in
21 geographic areas facing a critical shortage of child care, by
22 reducing the costs of operating a micro facility; and
23 (B) ensuring the health and safety of children for whom a
24 micro facility provides child care.
25 (b) In determining waivers or variances to be incorporated under
26 subsection (a)(2), the office of the secretary shall consider efficiencies
27 such as:
28 (1) allowing a micro facility to be operated in either a residential
29 or nonresidential building;
30 (2) prescribing educational requirements for staff members of a
31 micro facility that are tailored to the needs of providing child care
32 to groups of thirty (30) children or less; and
33 (3) allowing for supervision of children of diverse age groups in
34 a manner that maximizes use of limited facility space.
35 (c) Not later than March 1, 2025, the office of the secretary shall
36 establish and administer a pilot program under which:
37 (1) a licensee under IC 12-7-2-28.4 IC 12-7-2.1-55 or
38 IC 12-7-2-28.8 IC 12-7-2.1-58 that:
39 (A) operates an existing micro facility; or
40 (B) proposes to begin operating a new micro facility not more
41 than sixty (60) days after the date of the licensee's application
42 under this subdivision;
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

131
1 may apply to participate in the pilot program in a manner
2 prescribed by the office of the secretary;
3 (2) the office of the secretary shall select at least three (3)
4 licensees that apply under subdivision (1) and:
5 (A) allow a selected licensee described in subdivision (1)(A)
6 to operate the licensee's existing micro facility; and
7 (B) allow a selected licensee described in subdivision (1)(B)
8 to operate the licensee's proposed micro facility;
9 under the regulatory model developed under subsection (a); and
10 (3) the office of the secretary shall:
11 (A) monitor the operation of the micro facilities operating
12 under the regulatory model under subdivision (2); and
13 (B) evaluate the degree to which the operation of the micro
14 facilities under the regulatory model serves the balance
15 described in subsection (a)(3).
16 (d) The office of the secretary shall, to the extent practicable, select
17 licensees for participation in the pilot program such that the micro
18 facilities operated by the licensees are located in areas:
19 (1) that are geographically diverse from one another; and
20 (2) in which there exists a critical shortage of child care providers.
21 (e) A waiver or variance applied to a micro facility under this
22 section expires on the earlier of:
23 (1) the date specified by the office of the secretary; or
24 (2) December 31, 2026.
