15 (4) "Student" means an individual who:
16 (A) is more than five (5) years of age and less than
17 twenty-three (23) years of age;
18 (B) has been admitted to a facility; and
19 (C) was enrolled in a school corporation during the school year
20 immediately preceding the student's admission to the facility.
21 (b) This section applies to a student if:
22 (1) the student is placed in a facility under the written order of a
23 physician licensed under IC 25-22.5;
24 (2) the written order of the physician licensed under IC 25-22.5
25 is based on medical necessity, as determined by a physician
26 licensed under IC 25-22.5; and
27 (3) the student receives educational services provided by the
28 facility.
29 (c) A facility shall provide written notice to the school corporation
30 not later than five (5) business days (excluding weekends and holidays)
31 after a student described in subsection (b) is admitted to the facility.
32 The written notice must include the following:
33 (1) The student's name, address, and date of birth.
34 (2) The date on which the student was admitted to the facility.
35 (3) A copy of the physician's written order.
36 (4) A statement that the student has opted out of attending school
37 under section 8 of this chapter.
38 (5) A statement that the facility will provide all educational
39 services to the student during the student's admission in the
40 facility.
41 (d) The school corporation shall pay the facility a daily per diem as
42 determined under subsection (e) for the educational services provided
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

153
1 by the facility to the student during the student's admission in the
2 facility. The school corporation may not be required to pay for any
3 educational services provided to the student by the facility exceeding
