32 later than December 31 of each year that contains the following
33 information:
34 (1) A description of the processes:
35 (A) used to develop or select the medical necessity criteria for
36 coverage of services for treatment of a mental illness or
37 substance abuse; and
38 (B) used to develop or select the medical necessity criteria for
39 coverage of services for treatment of other medical or surgical
40 conditions.
41 (2) Identification of all nonquantitative treatment limitations that
42 are applied to:
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

177
1 (A) coverage of services for treatment of a mental illness or
2 substance abuse; and
3 (B) coverage of services for treatment of other medical or
4 surgical conditions;
5 within each classification of benefits.
6 (e) There may be no separate nonquantitative treatment limitations
7 that apply to coverage of services for treatment of a mental illness or
8 substance abuse that do not apply to coverage of services for treatment
9 of other medical or surgical conditions within any classification of
10 benefits.
11 (f) An insurer that issues a policy of accident and sickness insurance
12 that provides coverage of services for treatment of a mental illness or
13 substance abuse shall also submit an analysis showing the insurer's
14 compliance with this section and the act to the department not later
15 than December 31 of each year. The analysis must do the following:
16 (1) Identify the factors used to determine that a nonquantitative
17 treatment limitation will apply to a benefit, including factors that
18 were considered but rejected.
19 (2) Identify and define the specific evidentiary standards used to
20 define the factors and any other evidence relied upon in designing
21 each nonquantitative treatment limitation.
22 (3) Provide the comparative analyses, including the results of the
23 analyses, performed to determine the following:
24 (A) That the processes and strategies used to design each
25 nonquantitative treatment limitation for coverage of services
26 for treatment of a mental illness or substance abuse are
27 comparable to, and applied no more stringently than, the
28 processes and strategies used to design each nonquantitative
29 treatment limitation for coverage of services for treatment of
30 other medical or surgical conditions.
31 (B) That the processes and strategies used to apply each
32 nonquantitative treatment limitation for treatment of a mental
33 illness or substance abuse are comparable to, and applied no
34 more stringently than, the processes and strategies used to
35 apply each nonquantitative limitation for treatment of other
36 medical or surgical conditions.
37 (g) The department shall adopt rules to ensure compliance with this
38 section and the applicable provisions of the act.
