4 SECTION 163. IC 31-15-7-4 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
5 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4. (a) In an action for
6 dissolution of marriage under IC 31-15-2-2, the court shall divide the
7 property of the parties, whether:
8 (1) owned by either spouse before the marriage;
9 (2) acquired by either spouse in his or her own right:
10 (A) after the marriage; and
11 (B) before final separation of the parties; or
12 (3) acquired by their joint efforts.
13 (b) The court shall divide the property in a just and reasonable
14 manner by:
15 (1) division of the property in kind;
16 (2) setting the property or parts of the property over to one (1) of
17 the spouses and requiring either spouse to pay an amount, either
