5 (j) The applicant is responsible for any fees associated with a
6 criminal history check.
7 (k) The department shall, at the applicant's request, inform the
8 applicant as to whether the department has or does not have a record of
9 the person who is the subject of a criminal history check and whether
10 the department has identified the person as an alleged perpetrator of
11 abuse or neglect. The department may not provide to the applicant any
12 details or personally identifying information contained in any child
13 protective services investigation report.
14 (l) A person who is the subject of a criminal history check
15 conducted in accordance with this section may request the state police
16 department to provide the person with a copy of any state or national
17 criminal history report concerning the person.
