12 (c) When a juvenile court appoints a guardian ad litem or court
13 appointed special advocate in a proceeding from a volunteer based
14 program funded through IC 33-24-6-4, and, due to the caseload of the
15 guardian ad litem program or court appointed special advocate
16 program, the child is placed on a waiting list for guardian ad litem or
17 court appointed special advocate services:
18 (1) the guardian ad litem program or court appointed special
19 advocate program;
20 (2) any employee of or volunteer for the guardian ad litem
21 program or court appointed special advocate program; and
22 (3) any individual acting as a contracted guardian ad litem;
23 are immune from civil liability based on the child being placed on the
24 waiting list unless the placement of the child on the waiting list is the
25 result of gross negligence or willful and wanton misconduct.
26 (d) Nothing in this section shall be construed to negate the
27 appointment of a:
28 (1) guardian ad litem; or
29 (2) court appointed special advocate;
30 when required by IC 31-34-10-3.
