31 (2) the initiation of competency restoration services to a defendant
32 by a third party contractor;
33 the superintendent of the state institution (as defined in IC 12-7-2-184)
34 IC 12-7-2.1-318) or the director or medical director of the third party
35 contractor, if the division of mental health and addiction has entered
36 into a contract for the provision of competency restoration services by
37 a third party, shall certify to the proper court whether the defendant has
38 a substantial probability of attaining the ability to understand the
39 proceedings and assist in the preparation of the defendant's defense
40 within the foreseeable future.
41 (b) If a party files a motion to dismiss, the court may dismiss the
42 charges against the defendant without prejudice if the:
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

301
1 (1) defendant has been diagnosed with:
2 (A) dementia;
3 (B) Alzheimer's disease; or
4 (C) a traumatic brain injury;
5 (2) defendant's diagnosis substantially impacts the defendant's
6 ability to understand the proceedings and assist in the preparation
7 of the defendant's defense within the foreseeable future; and
8 (3) defendant is charged with a misdemeanor or a Level 6 felony.
9 (c) If a defendant's charges are not dismissed under subsection (b)
10 and a substantial probability does not exist, the state institution (as
11 defined in IC 12-7-2-184) IC 12-7-2.1-318) or the third party
12 contractor shall initiate regular commitment proceedings under
13 IC 12-26. If a substantial probability does exist, the state institution (as
14 defined in IC 12-7-2-184) IC 12-7-2.1-318) or third party contractor
15 shall retain the defendant:
16 (1) until the defendant attains the ability to understand the
17 proceedings and assist in the preparation of the defendant's
18 defense and is returned to the proper court for trial; or
19 (2) for six (6) months from the date of the:
20 (A) defendant's admission to a state institution (as defined in
21 IC 12-7-2-184); IC 12-7-2.1-318); or
22 (B) initiation of competency restoration services by a third
23 party contractor;
24 whichever first occurs.
