ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

308
1 and
2 (3) uses or exerts the law enforcement officer's professional
3 relationship with the child to engage with the child in:
4 (A) sexual intercourse;
5 (B) other sexual conduct (as defined in IC 35-31.5-2-221.5);
6 or
7 (C) any fondling or touching with the child with the intent to
8 arouse or satisfy the sexual desires of the child or the law
9 enforcement officer;
10 commits child seduction.
11 (s) In determining whether a person used or exerted the person's
