21 ethical obligations of the person's profession or occupation.
22 (4) The authority that the person had over the child.
23 (5) Whether the person exploited any particular vulnerability of
24 the child.
25 (6) Any other evidence relevant to the person's ability to exert
26 undue influence over the child.
