9 SECTION 237. IC 35-44.1-1-4, AS AMENDED BY P.L.158-2013,
10 SECTION 499, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
11 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4. (a) The following definitions
12 apply throughout this section:
13 (1) "Dependent" means any of the following:
14 (A) The spouse of a public servant.
15 (B) A child, stepchild, or adoptee (as defined in IC 31-9-2-2)
16 IC 31-9-2.1-8) of a public servant who is:
17 (i) unemancipated; and
18 (ii) less than eighteen (18) years of age.
19 (C) An individual more than one-half (1/2) of whose support
20 is provided during a year by the public servant.
21 (2) "Governmental entity served by the public servant" means the
22 immediate governmental entity being served by a public servant.
23 (3) "Pecuniary interest" means an interest in a contract or
24 purchase if the contract or purchase will result or is intended to
25 result in an ascertainable increase in the income or net worth of:
26 (A) the public servant; or
27 (B) a dependent of the public servant who:
28 (i) is under the direct or indirect administrative control of
29 the public servant; or
30 (ii) receives a contract or purchase order that is reviewed,
31 approved, or directly or indirectly administered by the public
32 servant.
33 (b) A public servant who knowingly or intentionally:
34 (1) has a pecuniary interest in; or
35 (2) derives a profit from;
36 a contract or purchase connected with an action by the governmental
37 entity served by the public servant commits conflict of interest, a Level
38 6 felony.
39 (c) It is not an offense under this section if any of the following
40 apply:
41 (1) The public servant or the public servant's dependent receives
42 compensation through salary or an employment contract for:
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

311
1 (A) services provided as a public servant; or
2 (B) expenses incurred by the public servant as provided by
3 law.
4 (2) The public servant's interest in the contract or purchase and all
5 other contracts and purchases made by the governmental entity
6 during the twelve (12) months before the date of the contract or
7 purchase was two hundred fifty dollars ($250) or less.
8 (3) The contract or purchase involves utility services from a utility
9 whose rate structure is regulated by the state or federal
10 government.
11 (4) The public servant:
12 (A) acts in only an advisory capacity for a state supported
13 college or university; and
14 (B) does not have authority to act on behalf of the college or
15 university in a matter involving a contract or purchase.
16 (5) A public servant under the jurisdiction of the state ethics
17 commission (as provided in IC 4-2-6-2.5) obtains from the state
18 ethics commission, following full and truthful disclosure, written
19 approval that the public servant will not or does not have a
20 conflict of interest in connection with the contract or purchase
21 under IC 4-2-6 and this section. The approval required under this
22 subdivision must be:
23 (A) granted to the public servant before action is taken in
24 connection with the contract or purchase by the governmental
25 entity served; or
26 (B) sought by the public servant as soon as possible after the
27 contract is executed or the purchase is made and the public
28 servant becomes aware of the facts that give rise to a question
29 of conflict of interest.
30 (6) A public servant makes a disclosure that meets the
31 requirements of subsection (d) or (e) and is:
32 (A) not a member or on the staff of the governing body
33 empowered to contract or purchase on behalf of the
34 governmental entity, and functions and performs duties for the
35 governmental entity unrelated to the contract or purchase;
36 (B) appointed by an elected public servant;
37 (C) employed by the governing body of a school corporation
38 and the contract or purchase involves the employment of a
39 dependent or the payment of fees to a dependent;
40 (D) elected; or
41 (E) a member of, or a person appointed by, the board of
42 trustees of a state supported college or university.
ES 80—LS 6159/DI 112

312
1 (7) The public servant is a member of the governing board of, or
2 is a physician employed or contracted by, a hospital organized or
3 operated under IC 16-22-1 through IC 16-22-5 or IC 16-23-1.
4 (d) A disclosure must:
5 (1) be in writing;
6 (2) describe the contract or purchase to be made by the
7 governmental entity;
8 (3) describe the pecuniary interest that the public servant has in
9 the contract or purchase;
10 (4) be affirmed under penalty of perjury;
11 (5) be submitted to the governmental entity and be accepted by
12 the governmental entity in a public meeting of the governmental
13 entity before final action on the contract or purchase;
14 (6) be filed within fifteen (15) days after final action on the
15 contract or purchase with:
16 (A) the state board of accounts; and
17 (B) if the governmental entity is a governmental entity other
18 than the state or a state supported college or university, the
19 clerk of the circuit court in the county where the governmental
20 entity takes final action on the contract or purchase; and
21 (7) contain, if the public servant is appointed, the written approval
22 of the elected public servant (if any) or the board of trustees of a
23 state supported college or university (if any) that appointed the
24 public servant.
25 (e) This subsection applies only to a person who is a member of, or
26 a person appointed by, the board of trustees of a state supported college
27 or university. A person to whom this subsection applies complies with
28 the disclosure requirements of this chapter with respect to the person's
29 pecuniary interest in a particular type of contract or purchase which is
30 made on a regular basis from a particular vendor if the individual files
31 with the state board of accounts and the board of trustees a statement
32 of pecuniary interest in that particular type of contract or purchase
33 made with that particular vendor. The statement required by this
34 subsection must be made on an annual basis.
